**TONIGHT: Queer Theatre Variety Night **
**Wednesday 4th February 2026**
üìçThe Two Brewers, Clapham

A proper queer night out, built around cabaret.

Expect a mixed bill of drag, stand-up, musical theatre, live music, spoken word, pop acts and queer cabaret. You‚Äôll see established performers sharing the best of their work alongside emerging artists stepping into the spotlight with something fresh.

With cabaret-style seating, it‚Äôs social by design. Come to watch, come to meet people, come to have a big joyful night in a queer-run room. And every ticket supports Queer Theatre‚Äôs work producing LGBTQIA+ stories and nurturing LGBTQIA+ theatre-makers.

**Cast:**
**Host: Jack Knave **‚òÖ Avital Kagan ‚òÖ Bobbi Dazzler ‚òÖ Bran Isabella ‚òÖ Dav Andrews ‚òÖ Fempath ‚òÖ Freddie Haberfellner ‚òÖ Lady Harmony Heaven ‚òÖ Josh Pullinger ‚òÖ Justin Elizabeth Sayer ‚òÖ Josh Sanchez ‚òÖ Pearl Does Country ‚òÖ Peter Pearl ‚òÖ Marsha Dean ‚òÖ Poet The Jules ‚òÖ Ri Baroche ‚òÖ Tooting Broadway ‚òÖ Yass Tina

After 40 years and nearly 1,300 bookings, I created The Actor Career Program to give actors the roadmap I wish I'd had when I was struggling early in my career.

Check it out: https://howtoactandmodel.com/the-actor-career-program

And as always, I'll keep sharing my free weekly tips here too!

That‚Äôs why policies around ùêúùê®ùêßùê¨ùêûùêßùê≠, ùê•ùê¢ùêúùêûùêßùê¨ùê¢ùêßùê†, and ùêúùê®ùê¶ùê©ùêûùêßùê¨ùêöùê≠ùê¢ùê®ùêß are essential. Without them, the tech gets used recklessly and creators pay the price. With them, AI can do what it‚Äôs best at: speeding up workflow and admin so artists can focus on what only humans can do ‚Äî ùêúùê´ùêöùêüùê≠, ùê≠ùêöùê¨ùê≠ùêû, ùê≠ùê´ùêÆùê≠ùê°.

**CASTING CALL ‚Äì JENNY & POPPY (Newcastle)** 

We are currently casting **two key female roles** for a Newcastle-based short film / pilot being produced as part of a university project.

**Roles:**

**JENNY (mid - late 20s)**
Confident, sharp, and socially switched-on. Jenny is witty, emotionally intelligent, and often the voice of reason within the group. Strong presence on screen.

**POPPY (mid - late 20s)**
Warm, expressive, and empathetic. Poppy is thoughtful and emotionally open, with a grounded and natural energy. A character with depth and subtlety.

 **Location:** Newcastle (Bar No.28 & The Last Resort)
 **Shoot dates:** First two weeks of February (starting 4th Feb) ‚Äì approx. **6 days availability required**
 **Unpaid student production** (travel support available)
 Great **showreel material + headshots provided**

Submission ends 1st February.

If interested, please get in touch:

 willm.patton@gmail.com
 07495 605757

Feel free to share with anyone who may be suitable.

Thank you!

Hi all! I am casting for my final short film ‚ÄòBody Electric‚Äô with the University of Warwick and London Film School, shooting THIS WEEKEND üé• in Coventry! 

This film follows a young dancer as she navigates the absurdity of the world's indifference, finding that ‚Äúworking harder‚Äù is simply not enough for success. 

Snacks/ drinks will be provided on set. Transport may be compensated depending on distance. This is a great opportunity to add professional footage to your showreel and get on-set experience ‚ò∫Ô∏è Read below for specific role descriptions:

GIRL 1: 18-24, any ethnicity. As the coach‚Äôs daughter who gets the role over the protagonist, she‚Äôs talented and hardworking, but aware that her last name opens doors others have to fight to pry open. She doesn‚Äôt flaunt it, doesn‚Äôt apologize for it either. This is NOT a dancing role.

GIRL 2: 18-24, any ethnicity. Girl 1‚Äôs best friend. Warm, perceptive, and socially fluent. She smooths over conflicts, sometimes at the cost of her own voice. This is NOT a dancing role.

CROWD: A ‚Äúpressing, engulfing crowd‚Äù around the protagonist.

üé§ *CASTING CALL* | PROFESSIONAL ON-SCREEN FEMALE PRESENTER
Required For |

Event: Wedding Exhibition Fair by Asiana Magazine

Where: üìç London, UK 

Date: Sunday 8th February 2026

Call Time Arrival and Wrap Time: 1:00PM till 4:00PM

K.A Global Production House is seeking a confident, bubbly, and professional Female Presenter to host interviews and provide news-style coverage at the Wedding Exhibition Fair organised by popular Royal Fashion Brand 'Asiana'. Interviewing the Exhibitors and briefly chatting to them asking them what their Brand/Business is about. 

This opportunity is ideal for those who are passionate about Fashion and Arts who want to build or expand their on-camera portfolio. At the function you are welcome to network for your own benefit which there will be high value individuals and groups from various professional backgrounds.

We also have lot's more functions coming up such as a private Charity Event taking place on 14th February 2026 and many other functions and projects. Which we will require a Presenter.

WHO WE‚ÄôRE LOOKING FOR?

Ages: 20's OR 30's

Fluent in English with strong voice projection

Naturally confident, energetic, and camera-friendly

Must be already based in London, UK or anyone who will be in London on that date and time

Interested in building experience, portfolio, credentials and industry connections

PLATFORM DISTRIBUTION |

Content Will Be Released On:

- Social Media Platforms

- YouTube

- K.A Global Homepage

Some Highlighted clips may be seen on South Asian Desi Television Network

WHAT YOU‚ÄôLL GAIN?

Added to K.A Global Casting Database

Support in building a professional portfolio

Introductions to Agents and Agency contacts

Consideration for future K.A Global projects, events and presenting roles

Opportunity to be considered as a Brand Ambassador

HOW TO APPLY?

Inbox The Following:

- Full Name

- Social Media Handles

- Portfolio 'If You Own One'

- Contact Information

Shortlisted applicants will receive a 5-minute phone call to discuss the event, interview style, and details.

SERIOUS APPLICANTS ONLY

Confirmed applicants for the 8th February event will be contacted Saturday morning (day before event).

The applicants not selected for this date may be contacted in advance for our 14th February 2026 Charity Event.

We are actively scouting long-term talents for upcoming projects and functions to join our team. We take Pride in those who have potential.

K.A Global ¬©

Building Creative Futures

message.text:
What an incredible evening it was to be interviewed by the wonderful Victoria Beale Live with a studio audience at the 'Business Growth Crowd - Global Podcast Networking with New London media in London bridge today! 

I had the chance to share insights from my journey of standing up against the hostile infiltrations in our world while also promoting my upcoming short film premiere, 'Where are the Children?' 

The full interview is in the editing stage right now, but I wanted to share this snippet in the meantime!
....................................................................................

Grab tickets here for my Premier 'Where are the children'? üëáüèæ

https://aleytonbentashortfilmpremier.eventbrite.co.uk

Saturday 28th February from 7pm to 9:30pm at the Rich Mix London 
¬£10.00 for tickets üéü

#leytonbenta #globalpodcast #leytonbentawherearethechildren
#speakonout #newlondonmedia

Building a festival from the ground up takes a village! ‚ù§Ô∏è
The ettc is a small non-profit with a big vision. To keep our festival sustainable, we aren't able to provide hotel accommodation this year‚Äîbut we ARE launching a "Host an Artist" program to connect our performers with the local community.

If you‚Äôre an artist who values grassroots connection over fancy hotels, we want you. If you're a local who wants to host a creator, stay tuned! üè†

Check the FAQ and apply today: www.ettc.pl/SoloStage

So here we go again for CANNES 202‚Äã6! For those of you that were with me last year, you know the coup!  This year we have our super swanky villa for 8 nights' from the 1‚Äã2th to the ‚Äã2‚Äã0th of May (8 nights), so essentially for almost the duration of the entire festival ‚Äãa‚Äãnd the cost will be ¬£1,250 per person or ¬£‚Äã2‚Äã,500 per‚Äã t‚Äãwin room‚Äã which includes breakfast at the villa, 'exclusive' VIP tickets for the MAGNIFICENT FILMS party and of course 'exclusive' VIP tickets to any other industry soir√©es that we will be having at the villa (TBA). As residents of the villa you will also be able to have your own ‚Äãsmall daytime industry 'networking soir√©es' too‚Äã. If you want to do a bigger event in the evening (more than 50 guests) ‚Äãthere will be an additional cost as last year one of our guests had a huge event which needed a lot of work and management, details and costs upon request! 
If you‚Äôre interested, DM me here or email Harriet, who will be running villa admin this year:
üì© harriet@magnificentfilms.co.uk
Hope to see you in CANNES! ü•Ç‚ú®

Hi everyone! Is anyone looking for voice lessons? I'm excited to share that I have a handful of openings in my online holistic voice studio!

Students learn to perform with passion and sing what they love. They gain confidence with their vocal technique and emotional expression. The studio is an open, safe environment for students of all abilities and specializes in supporting kids & adults with ADHD and Autism.

I offer a complimentary consultation to learn more about your voice and your goals, and ensure it is the right fit. Pls comment below for more details, and I will send you a DM!

**Deepen Your Truth, Presence & Craft ‚Äì Meisner Workshop in Helsinki** üåü
**February 18-19   I   with Nita Arpiainen**

Do you ever feel like your acting is better when you‚Äôre performing alone? Free, relaxed, and without anyone watching, yet struggling to access that same truth on set, in auditions, or in front of the camera.

Many actors experience this: moments of effortless expression alone, yet pressure from cameras, lines, and instructions seem to block the same authenticity in real settings. The challenge isn‚Äôt your talent. It‚Äôs learning to **bring that truthful acting in front of an audience with more ease and confidence**.

That‚Äôs what **Authentic Me**, our two-evening Meisner Technique workshop is designed to do. Through exercises that build presence, impulse, and truthful connection, you‚Äôll learn to **access your authentic acting anywhere ‚Äî on stage, on set, and in auditions**.

**You‚Äôll learn how to:**
‚ú® Respond truthfully without planning or performing
‚ú® Access your authentic emotional impulses
‚ú® Listen to & build deeper connection with your scene partners
‚ú® Release tension and overthinking
‚ú® Trust your instincts and impulses
‚ú® React naturally, creating honest & compelling behavior

And this all within a very safe space and a supportive group.

Open to actors, directors, writers, creatives, and anyone who wants to live and relate more authentically. No previous experience needed! 

**Limited spots ‚Äì Reserve your spot now:**
[https://www.actorsacademy.fi/authentic-me

](https://www.actorsacademy.fi/authentic-me)*‚ÄúAn exceptionally guided introduction to the Meisner technique. Nita‚Äôs deep understanding of the work creates a safe, precise and playful space where authentic acting emerges naturally. Powerful not only for your craft, but for how you listen, respond and live.‚Äù*

**Feb 18‚Äì19, 2026 (Wed & Thu)**

**Castingaufruf f√ºr studentischen Kurzfilm (T√ºbinale)**

Meine studentische Filmgruppe sucht Darsteller*innen f√ºr einen ca. 6-min√ºtigen Kurzfilm, der im Rahmen der T√ºbinale entsteht. Gedreht wird in der Fildergegend nahe Stuttgart. Der genaue Drehzeitraum wird noch bekannt gegeben.

**Logline:**
Als eine junge Frau beginnt, ihre Beziehung mit einem anderen Paar zu vergleichen, verliert sie den Blick f√ºr die Liebe, die direkt vor ihr steht.

**Gesuchte Rollen (alle ca. 19‚Äì25 Jahre):**

**Weibliche Hauptrolle**
Junge Frau in ihrer ersten ernsthaften Beziehung. Unsicher, emotional offen, stark von √§u√üeren Erwartungen und Vergleichen beeinflusst. Die Rolle erfordert ein sensibles Spiel innerer Konflikte und leiser emotionaler Ver√§nderungen.

**M√§nnliche Hauptrolle**
Ihr Freund. Bodenst√§ndig, ruhig und bem√ºht. Er liebt ehrlich, ger√§t aber zunehmend unter Druck, weil er den Erwartungen seiner Partnerin nicht gerecht werden kann. Subtiles, zur√ºckgenommenes Spiel ist wichtig.

**Weibliche Nebenrolle**
Junge Frau mit perfekter Au√üenwirkung. Kontrolliert und diszipliniert, privat jedoch angespannt. Die Rolle lebt vom Kontrast zwischen √§u√üerer Kontrolle und innerer Unsicherheit.

**M√§nnliche Nebenrolle**
Charismatisch, dominant, stark auf Au√üenwirkung bedacht. Kontrollierend und schnell reizbar. Muss zwischen Charme und unterschwelliger Bedrohlichkeit wechseln k√∂nnen.

Schauspielerfahrung ist willkommen, aber keine Voraussetzung. Wichtig sind Verl√§sslichkeit, Lust auf Spielen und Interesse an einem emotionalen, beziehungszentrierten Stoff.
Bei Interesse einfach eine Nachricht schreiben, dann schicken wir weitere Infos und das Drehbuch.

CASTING CALL ‚Äî PRINCE SALIM 
Anarkali Reimagined | Immersive Theatre

A prince in love.
An empire in the way.
A choice that changes everything.

We‚Äôre casting Prince Salim for the remount of Anarkali Reimagined ‚Äî a powerful immersive love story about defying power, legacy, and expectation for the sake of the heart.

‚ú® Open to actors of all ethnicities
‚ú® Previously played by a Hispanic actor
‚ú® Casting for presence, emotional depth, and mindset ‚Äî not a specific look

THE ROLE
Prince Salim is passionate, conflicted, rebellious, and deeply loyal. Think Romeo with political consequence. Requires emotional range, stamina, and comfort performing in close proximity to an audience.

ROLE DETAILS
‚Ä¢ Male, late 20s‚Äìmid 30s
‚Ä¢ Strong English | no accent required
‚Ä¢ Collaborative, curious, emotionally grounded
‚Ä¢ Movement experience a plus

TIMELINE
‚Ä¢ Rehearsals begin August
‚Ä¢ Performances late October
‚Ä¢ Houston-based | evenings/weekends

AUDITIONS
Self-tape only
Rolling submissions

TO APPLY
Email headshot + resume (if available) + a short note on why this role speaks to you to:
üìß dreamershtx@gmail.com
Subject: Prince Salim Audition

We‚Äôre looking for actors who want to build something meaningful, not just book a credit.

topComments.text: Important note: This is currently an unpaid role as part of a remount of a well-received production, with potential for future paid extensions or growth. Transparency matters to us ‚Äî thank you for your understanding.

I‚Äôm a UK actor looking to connect with filmmakers developing new work.

**Deepen Your Truth, Presence & Craft ‚Äì Meisner Workshop in Helsinki** üåü
**February 18-19   I   with Nita Arpiainen**

Do you ever feel like your acting is better when you‚Äôre performing alone? Free, relaxed, and without anyone watching, yet struggling to access that same truth on set, in auditions, or in front of the camera.

Many actors experience this: moments of effortless expression alone, yet pressure from cameras, lines, and instructions seem to block the same authenticity in real settings. The challenge isn‚Äôt your talent. It‚Äôs learning to **bring that truthful acting in front of an audience with more ease and confidence**.

That‚Äôs what **Authentic Me**, our two-evening Meisner Technique workshop is designed to do. Through exercises that build presence, impulse, and truthful connection, you‚Äôll learn to **access your authentic acting anywhere ‚Äî on stage, on set, and in auditions**.

**You‚Äôll learn how to:**
‚ú® Respond truthfully without planning or performing
‚ú® Access your authentic emotional impulses
‚ú® Listen to & build deeper connection with your scene partners
‚ú® Release tension and overthinking
‚ú® Trust your instincts and impulses
‚ú® React naturally, creating honest & compelling behavior

And this all within a very safe space and a supportive group.

Open to actors, directors, writers, creatives, and anyone who wants to live and relate more authentically. No previous experience needed! 

**Limited spots ‚Äì Reserve your spot now:**
[https://www.actorsacademy.fi/authentic-me

](https://www.actorsacademy.fi/authentic-me)*‚ÄúAn exceptionally guided introduction to the Meisner technique. Nita‚Äôs deep understanding of the work creates a safe, precise and playful space where authentic acting emerges naturally. Powerful not only for your craft, but for how you listen, respond and live.‚Äù*

**Feb 18‚Äì19, 2026 (Wed & Thu)**
**16:00‚Äì21:00**
**Actors Academy Studio, Helsinki**

Watch our video on the fear we often feel of not belonging or not being accepted: [https://www.instagram.com/p/DUTJctuDbyF/

](https://www.instagram.com/p/DUTJctuDbyF/)üå± Step into your **truth, presence, and creative power**.

CASTING CALL ‚Äì ACTORS
We‚Äôre looking for actors and actresses over 18 to join our upcoming non-commercial audio project, 2024, and help bring fast-paced, cinematic stories to life.

Date needed: 26th February

What we‚Äôre looking for:

‚Ä¢ Strong voice performers with clear delivery and emotional range

‚Ä¢ Actors comfortable performing intense, action-driven scenes for audio

‚Ä¢ Previous acting or voice acting experience is a plus (but not essential)

‚Ä¢ Reliable, collaborative, and able to take direction

This is a passion-led audio series and a great chance to be part of a creatively ambitious, story-focused project with a cinematic feel.

Interested?

Send an email to: gearhead.official.casting@gmail.com

Include:

‚Ä¢ A brief introduction

‚Ä¢ Any relevant acting or voice experience

‚Ä¢ A showreel or voice sample if you have one

We‚Äôll send an audition script to suitable applicants.

Let‚Äôs make something amazing!!

topComments.text:
I‚Äôm sorry but asking for a self-tape at the application stage is completely unprofessional. 

Self-tapes should only be requested once an application has been made and those who have been successful to the audition stage should be invited/requested to tape. 

Asking actors/actresses to send a self-tape in at the initial application is a waste of your time and most importantly the applicants time. It does not guarantee that the tapes will be watched or get a response. 

Self-tapes take a lot of effort and time to set up. From learning the lines, to setting up the camera, to getting the lighting right, editing it and sending it off. It‚Äôs a full time job in itself.

I have been a full time professional actor for 15 years and not once have I ever been asked to send a tape along with my initial application.

üé¨ DENVER / AURORA FILMMAKERS ‚Äî VOLUNTEER CREW CALL (IMDb CREDIT) üé¨
I‚Äôm filming a documentary in Lyons, CO on Monday, February 9, and I‚Äôm looking for a small volunteer crew‚Äîespecially a Director of Photography‚Äîto help capture an important story.

This film has been built entirely by volunteers‚Äîpeople who believe stories can actually change systems. We‚Äôre keeping the crew small, intentional, and respectful of everyone‚Äôs time.

### üé• Roles Needed:

‚Ä¢ Director of Photography (priority)  

‚Ä¢ Assistant Camera (AC)  

‚Ä¢ Lighting / Gaffer  

‚Ä¢ Production Assistant (PA)

### üìç Shoot Details:

üìÖ Monday, Feb 9  

üìç Anschutz Medical Campus ‚Äì Aurora, CO  

üéû Documentary (mental health, prevention, community)  

üé¨ IMDb credit provided  

‚è± Short, focused shoot day

This project centers on mental health prevention, belonging, and real human stories‚Äînot spectacle, not fluff. If you‚Äôre a DP or crew member who cares about purpose-driven filmmaking, meaningful collaboration, and telling stories that actually matter, I‚Äôd love to connect.

Please comment or DM with:

‚Ä¢ The role you‚Äôre interested in  

‚Ä¢ A link to your work, reel, or IG (if you have one)

Even sharing this with someone in your network helps more than you know.  

Thank you üíô

items.text:
Title: Saturdays

Genre: Thriller/Comedy

Logline: After accidentally taking a new designer drug on the way to a Halloween party, three broke nobodies become viral vigilantes in a city on the edge but their rise to infamy puts them in the cross-hairs of a charismatic cartel leader.

Role:

Dave (30-50) Unkillable, unshakable, and possibly unmedicated. Somehow still endearing. Dave is an uber driver, a hype man, and a secret weapon and comes from a different era. He‚Äôs the uncle at thanksgiving that you hope didn‚Äôt bring a bottle of scotch (you know he did). A chaotic wildcard who might be a genius... or just very, very lucky.

Production Type: Indie

Production Company: Loste Films

Contact Information: [luke@lostefilms.com](mailto:luke@lostefilms.com)

Run Time: Feature

Compensation: Catering/Crafty provided during proof of concept shoot. Compensation for future shoot dates is open to negotiation.

Audition Information: Send an email with headshot, resume and reel. The first round of auditions will be self-tape, then we will have in-person callbacks (downtown Denver area).

Shooting Schedule: Late February. Other shoot dates TBD

Filming Location: Highlands Ranch and Denver area

Project Description: Saturdays is an upcoming feature film we‚Äôre currently shooting the beginning of to use as a proof of concept. The scenes in the proof of concept are still being used in the final movie, which will be shot later on in the year. Due to scheduling conflicts we had to recast this role and are looking for someone who can carry mystery, comedy, and spiritual invincibility. There‚Äôs also lots of room for improv in the role. Some character inspirations include Erlich Eachman (Silicon Valley), Frank Reynolds (It‚Äôs Always Sunny), Red (Pineapple Express), Jay (Clerks), The Dude (The Big Lebowski). Attached pictures are the location/vehicles we have locked in for the first scene you‚Äôll be shooting with us.

IMDB Link: [https://www.imdb.com/title/tt39423188/](https://www.imdb.com/title/tt39423188/)

Requirement for Our Client‚Äôs Upcoming Feature Film

We are currently seeking talented and committed professionals to join our client‚Äôs upcoming Feature Film project. We aim to collaborate with passionate individuals who bring professionalism, creativity, and dedication to quality storytelling.

1. Assistant Director (AD)
   ‚Ä¢ Prior experience in films, web series, short films, or related media preferred
   ‚Ä¢ Strong organizational, coordination, and communication skills
   ‚Ä¢ Ability to manage schedules, support creative execution, and coordinate cast & crew
   ‚Ä¢ Must be responsible, punctual, and adaptable to dynamic shoot environments

   ‚Ä¢ Age Group: 18‚Äì35 years

For more details:

NATIONALLY SYNDICATED COURT SHOW IS LOOKING FOR MARRIED & LONG-TERM COUPLES WHO WANT HELP OR CLOSURE

A nationally syndicated court show is seeking real married couples and long-term partners who are on the verge of breaking up and need answers, resolution, or closure.

We are especially interested in couples with years of history and real-life stakes, including shared children, finances, property, or businesses.

Are you and your spouse facing any of the following?

‚Ä¢ Are you married and ready to call it quits, but need answers first?

‚Ä¢ Do you suspect your spouse or long-term partner is cheating?

‚Ä¢ Is your spouse accusing you of cheating and/or denying your child?

‚Ä¢ Have years of marriage led you to a breaking point where you need closure?

‚Ä¢ Do you have evidence your spouse or long-term partner has been unfaithful and want to confront them?

‚Ä¢ Is your spouse‚Äôs behavior tearing your family or marriage apart?

‚Ä¢ Are bad habits or addictions damaging your marriage and affecting your children?

‚Ä¢ Have ongoing trust issues made it impossible to move forward in your marriage?

‚Ä¢ Are in-laws or extended family interfering in your marriage?

‚Ä¢ Are you in a long-term marriage with unresolved financial betrayal or disputes?

‚Ä¢ Are you married with children and need answers for the sake of your family‚Äôs future?

‚Ä¢ Have you reached the final straw in a long-term marriage and need resolution?

WHO WE ARE LOOKING FOR:

‚Ä¢ Married couples

‚Ä¢ Engaged couples

‚Ä¢ Long-term couples (4+ years preferred) with real stakes involved

‚Ä¢ Shared children

‚Ä¢ Shared finances

‚Ä¢ Shared property (home, apartment, vehicles)

‚Ä¢ Shared business or major life commitments

‚Ä¢ LGBTQ+ married and long-term couples

WHAT‚ÄôS INCLUDED:

‚Ä¢ One-day court show appearance

‚Ä¢ Couples counseling / marriage counseling support

‚Ä¢ Lie detector testing (if applicable)

‚Ä¢ DNA testing (if applicable)

üëâ All testing and services are provided and paid for by production.

Click the link below or copy and paste to bowser 

[https://seekingmarriedlongtermcouplesinrelationshipsnationwidecasting.castingcrane.com/](https://seekingmarriedlongtermcouplesinrelationshipsnationwidecasting.castingcrane.com/)

items.text:
I am currently Producing a brand new show for Channel 4 in creating an alternative court to resolve your disputes, without the usual costs and delays.

Has a dispute got out of hand?

Do you want to draw a line under a conflict that‚Äôs been going on too long?

In this brand-new series, from the makers of *Long Lost Family,* we‚Äôll open the doors of a fast-track court that will help people settle their civil disputes.

All those who take part will be provided with **free expert legal representation**.

**We are looking for people who would like to sort out a dispute in a swift and legally-binding hearing.**

Why should you take part?
* Do you feel that you are owed money, an apology, or simply justice on a matter?
Perhaps you want a refund on a service you paid for? Whatever the issue, big or small, this could be your chance to have your story heard and to reach a final verdict.
* Perhaps the civil court system feels too complex, too costly, or just takes too long.
* Perhaps you‚Äôd like the free advice of some of Britain‚Äôs top lawyers (likely in region of ¬£10,000)

**If you want to apply or have a no obligation conversation with someone to find out more then drop me a message**

**** We cannot dispute anything against councils - this would be a person to person claim - we have also reached out capacity for car cases and rogue traders ****

sharedPost.text:
AUDITION ANNOUNCEMENT

King Lear by William Shakespeare

A Virtual Staged Reading
Presented by Curtain Call Virtual Productions

Curtain Call Virtual Productions is proud to announce auditions for a virtual staged reading of William Shakespeare‚Äôs monumental tragedy King Lear.

Audition Date:
Sunday, February 22nd
7:30 p.m. BST / 2:30 p.m. EST / 11:30 a.m. PST

Held Virtually (via Zoom)

PRODUCTION TEAM
Co-Directed by: Colin Albo & Ashley Marsh

Original Script by: William Shakespeare

Edits & Language Modernization by: Colin Albo

HOW TO REGISTER
To register for auditions, participants must complete both of the following steps:

Email your headshot and theatrical r√©sum√© to

curtaincallvirtualproductions@gmail.com

Fill out the audition form linked on either the event page or the Facebook announcement

Once registration is complete, all auditioning actors will receive an email containing a PDF of the audition sides, which will be read during the audition.

No advanced preparation is required.

This is a staged reading, and multiple roles will be doubled.

All roles are open unless otherwise noted.

Please note: the role of Oswald has already been cast.

Important note: Due to the violence and mature content contained throughout the play, absolutely nobody under the age of 18 is allowed to audition! Absolutely no exceptions!

ROLES AVAILABLE
King Lear
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Late 40s‚ÄìEarly 60s
The aging King of Britain whose decision to divide his kingdom based on his daughters‚Äô professions of love sets the tragedy in motion. His journey from absolute authority to madness and painful self-knowledge is the heart of the play.

Goneril
Lead Role | Female Presenting | Playing Age: Late 20s‚ÄìMid 30s
Lear‚Äôs eldest daughter; ruthless, power-hungry, and manipulative. Married to the Duke of Albany. Embodies cruelty and ingratitude.

Regan
Lead Role | Female Presenting | Playing Age: Mid 20s‚ÄìEarly 30s
Lear‚Äôs middle daughter; equally cruel, often more sadistic than Goneril. Married to the Duke of Cornwall. Acts as Goneril‚Äôs partner in stripping Lear of power and dignity.

Cordelia
Lead Role | Female Presenting | Playing Age: Late Teens‚ÄìEarly 20s
Lear‚Äôs youngest daughter; honest, principled, and loving despite her refusal to flatter him. Marries the King of France and becomes Queen of France. Represents moral truth and emotional integrity.
Doubles as: The Fool ‚Äî Lear‚Äôs companion and truth-teller who uses wit and riddles to expose harsh truths.

Gloucester
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Early 40s‚ÄìLate 60s
A nobleman whose story parallels Lear‚Äôs: a father misjudging his children. Father of Edmund and Edgar. His blinding and suffering mirror Lear‚Äôs descent into madness.

Edmund
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Late Teens‚ÄìEarly 20s
Gloucester‚Äôs illegitimate son; ambitious, clever, and morally corrupt. A driving antagonist whose manipulation fuels much of the play‚Äôs violence.

Edgar
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Mid 20s‚ÄìLate 30s
Gloucester‚Äôs legitimate son; loyal, moral, and forced into disguise as ‚ÄúPoor Tom‚Äù to help his father. Represents endurance, redemption, and survival.

Albany
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Late 20s‚ÄìMid 30s
Goneril‚Äôs husband. Albany begins the play restrained and politically cautious, overshadowed by stronger personalities. As the kingdom fractures, he develops a moral spine, ultimately rejecting cruelty and asserting principled leadership. Doubles as: Doctor, Knight, Curan

Cornwall
Lead Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Mid 20s‚ÄìEarly 30s
Regan‚Äôs spouse and a ruthless enforcer of authority. Impulsive, violent, and tyrannical, Cornwall embodies unchecked authoritarianism and the danger of power without empathy. Doubles as: Gentleman, Herald, Old Man

Kent
Supporting Role | Any Gender | Playing Age: Late 40s‚ÄìEarly 60s
A fiercely loyal noble and trusted advisor to Lear. Blunt, principled, and courageous to the point of self-sacrifice, Kent is banished for speaking truth to power and disguises themself to continue serving Lear in exile. Doubles as: Duke of Burgundy, Messenger

Oswald (CAST)
Supporting Role | Male Presenting | Playing Age: Any Age
Goneril‚Äôs primary servant. Endlessly obedient, Oswald follows any and all instructions from his mistress without considering their moral implications, rendering him cruel and heartless in her shadow.
Doubles as: King of France, Servant 1

Performers of all backgrounds are encouraged to audition.

This production embraces non-traditional casting and aims to assemble a strong ensemble to explore the power, cruelty, and humanity at the heart of King Lear.

https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScHMbtYTBlReh1AvrRsYaDtGR0nPaMaNMleJO2BZIw-D4quWw/viewform?usp=header

**CASTING CALL ‚Äî Multigenerational Family - Freelance Preferred **

We‚Äôre looking for a warm, authentic **multigenerational family** (grandparents, parents, and children) to appear in an upcoming **product branding photo/video shoot **for Balance of Nature. We‚Äôre seeking real families or talent groups who naturally represent connection, joy, and everyday moments together.

**Who we‚Äôre looking for:**
* Families representing 2‚Äì3 generations
   * Female & Male Talent Ages 50+ 
   * Female & Male Talent Ages 30+ 
   * Children ages 5+
* All ethnicities encouraged to apply
* Comfortable on camera and able to interact naturally together
* Families together are welcome to apply, but if it‚Äôs just you individually please apply as well because we might be able to cast you together with others. 

**Shoot details:**
* Location: St. George, UT
* Date(s): End of February
* Compensation: $65-$85/hr depending on experience. We can also do daily rates for full families, if hired. 
* Usage: Brand marketing and advertising materials. **Freelance preferred.** 

**To submit:**
Please send recent family photos, names/ages of participants, location, and contact information to [abustillo@bonadmin.com](mailto:abustillo@bonadmin.com) with the subject line **‚ÄúMultigenerational Family Casting.‚Äù**

We can‚Äôt wait to meet your family!

All serious inquires and for more details; please comment on this post or reach out to Def-G Productions directly at Defgpros@gmail.com

items.text:
CASTING CALL 
Lost Boy of the Cross is a short dramatic film (approx. 20 minutes) based on true events, exploring the childhood and early adolescence of Ray, a boy raised within Australia‚Äôs institutional care system and later abandoned to the streets of Sydney. The film follows Ray from early adolescence into his teenage years, revealing how abuse, neglect, faith, and enforced silence shaped his life long before he had the power to choose his own path.

This story is based on the life of Ray Leary, as documented in A Beautiful Boy by Kate Shayler.

We are casting an actor to portray Ray at age 14‚Äì15. This is a central, emotionally grounded role requiring strong screen presence and restraint. Ray is observant, guarded, and resilient

carrying trauma beneath the surface rather than expressing it outwardly.

Role details:

Male actor

Blonde hair, blue eyes

Actor must be 18+, but convincingly appear 14‚Äì15 years old

Naturalistic performance style essential

Non tied role (does not restrict future or concurrent work)

Acting experience welcomed but not mandatory

The story uses King's Cross as a narrative backbone not as legend or spectacle, but as the place where children failed by institutions were left to survive on their own.

Lost Boy of the Cross is intended for Australian and international film festivals, alongside selected industry, educational, and advocacy screenings. This is a trauma informed production led by an experienced director, with care, safety, and respect at the centre of the process. Full credit provided.

Email show real to albionlaneproductions@gmail.com

üè† LOCATION SCOUT: Cinematic House needed for Short Film (London)
Hi everyone! I am a director currently in pre-production for 'The Collector', a supernatural horror short that explores the nature of darkness and the strength found in vulnerability.

We are looking for our primary location: A house in London with a 'lived-in' feel. Specifically, we need a bedroom that feels like a sanctuary of memories and a living room with a fireplace.

Why host us? We are a dedicated, professional crew (The Resilient Idealist production style) committed to a quiet, respectful shoot. As a thank you, we offer:

Full 'Filming Location' credit in the movie.

Professional photos of your home (shot by our DP).

An invitation to the private screening.

A small 'thank you' hamper and our eternal gratitude!

If you or someone you know has a space that might fit this 'subconscious' aesthetic, please DM me for more details on the project and our safety protocols. Let‚Äôs bring some light into the dark together! ‚ú®"

And also here some of our stuff. Thank you

items.text:
Friends!

The Film Program at Cinematic Arts at CCA (formerly The Colorado Film School) invites actors of all ages to participate in our Spring 2026 Open Auditions!

Our student filmmakers are casting for a wide range of short films, narrative projects, and cinematic productions, and we are seeking performers of all backgrounds, ages, and experience levels to help bring these stories to life on screen.

Whether you are a seasoned professional, a student, or someone who simply loves acting, you are warmly invited to audition and collaborate with the next generation of filmmakers.

üìÖ Audition Dates & Times

Friday, February 6, 2026

üïô 10:00 a.m. ‚Äì 5:00 p.m.

Saturday, February 7, 2026

üïô 10:00 a.m. ‚Äì 4:00 p.m.

 

üìç Location

Lowry Studios ‚Äì Community College of Aurora

9075 E. Lowry Blvd.

Denver, CO 80230

 

üé≠ What to Prepare

Please bring a 2‚Äì3 minute prepared monologue for your primary audition.

In addition to the main audition, we will also host Satellite Auditions for specific student film productions:

‚Ä¢ These will take place in rooms throughout the building

‚Ä¢ Auditions are first-come, first-served

‚Ä¢ Actors can sign up to cold read for individual projects

‚Ä¢ We anticipate up to 10 productions casting during this event

‚Ä¢ A list of roles and productions will be available on the day of the audition

‚Ä¢ Participation in satellite auditions is optional, but highly encouraged

 

üìù How to Sign Up

Actors can sign up using the QR code on the flyer or by visiting:

Accessible Web Link:

https://www.ccaurora.edu/open-auditions

(For visually impaired users or anyone unable to scan the QR code, this link provides full access to the sign-up form.)

If you can't find a reserved space that works for you, come anyway during your preferred time. We will work you into the schedule!

We can't wait to see you this Friday or Saturday!

 

üì© Questions?

Please contact:

galina.boulgakova@ccaurora.edu

 üé• Help our students tell their stories through the magic of cinema.

items.text:
Hello all, we are looking for actors for a CU Denver student film shooting this march 

Title: The Scare

Genre: Drama, Period 

Synopsis: Terry is a normal kid having a normal childhood, with two small exceptions: her father is an American spy living in West Berlin at the height of the Cold War, and she is gradually going deaf in both ears. Every day she goes to school, does her homework, plays with dolls, and every night her family plays a game of "Scare," which unbeknownst to her, is preparation for an impending Russian invasion

Roles - 

Terry Galloway (10-12): A young girl trying to live a normal life in Berlin during the Cold War. She's also going deaf in both ears. Terry is feisty but afraid of the immense changes undertaking her life.

Trudy Galloway (14-15): Terry's older sister, anxious and too aware for her own good. 

Tenley Galloway (7-8): Terry's little sister, naive and oblivious. 

Paul (30-40): Terry's father, and a spy for the American military during the Cold War. Kind, good natured, and a natural liar.

Edna (25-40): Terry's mother. Anxious about the fate of her children. 

Edith (25-40): The family's maid. (German accent required)

Note: additional smaller roles needed, not listed 

Director, Writer: Sophii Sherman 

Based on: Mean Little Deaf Queer, Written by Terry Galloway

Producers: Dominic Spacone, Christine Galvez

Production Type: Student Film

Contact Information: Sophiisherman@gmail.com

Run Time: Short (~10 mins)

Compensation: Unpaid

Union Status: Non-Union

Audition Information: Auditions are all online and will be reviewed and casted this February 

Shooting Schedule: ~mar 12-22 - 4 day shooting schedule will fall sometime within that time span depending on actor availability

Filming Location: Denver

If you are interested scan the QR code or email and reach out!

items.text:
Hi all,
I am excited to announce that I am the director for an upcoming short film "Baller".

"Baller" is a short drama about a former professional footballer who projects his unfulfilled dreams onto his ten-year-old daughter - until he realises her happiness matters more than his legacy.

With the current crisis of youth teams picking up players younger than ever, "Baller" aims to spread awareness of this issue and the toxicity it can bring to parent-child relationships.

Any questions regarding this casting call or the project in general. Please feel free to send them to our email address:

BallerShortFilm@outlook.com

**UNRAVEL** is a short psychological thriller exploring dissociation, betrayal, and the quiet violence of denial. The film is performance-led and naturalistic, prioritising subtle emotional storytelling over overt horror, with a strong focus on character and atmosphere.

 

**EDDY The  *****Husband***

**Production Type:** Short Film
**Playing Age:** 40‚Äì55
**Gender:** Male
**Accent:** British
**Ethnicity:** Any
**Location Required:** London / Surrey

**Shoot:** **1 day**
**Provisional Timing:** **Mid-March (dates TBC)**
**Remuneration:** **¬£100 for the day**

**Character Overview:**
Charming, distracted, and casually affectionate. Eddy hides a devastating secret. He must feel like a believable, loving husband until the truth explodes.

Strong naturalism and subtext-driven performance essential. Actor must be comfortable playing emotional concealment, intimacy, and sudden tonal shifts.

 

**ROBBIE  *****The Lover***

**Playing Age:** 30‚Äì45
**Gender:** Male
**Accent:** British
**Ethnicity:** Any
**Location Required:** London / Surrey

**Shoot:** **1 day**
**Provisional Timing:** **Mid-March (dates TBC)**
**Remuneration:** **¬£100 for the day**

Intense, physical, emotionally impulsive. Robbie is Eddy‚Äôs secret partner and the emotional fuse of the story.

Requires comfort with confrontation, intimacy, and high emotional stakes.

Please send your information to kate@pilgrimagepictures.uk

Stage West Playhouse along with director Mathew Root and assistant director Jacob Mandelin are thrilled to announce auditions for "The Glass Menagerie".

IMPORTANT DATES:
Audition Dates: February 6 at 7 PM and February 8 at 1 PM, at the playhouse
Show Dates: April 24-26

AUDITION REQUIREMENTS:
Auditions will consist of cold readings. Video auditions will be accepted until 1 PM on February 8. Video auditions must include your name, address, phone number and email, as well as if you are auditioning for a specific role. Please include any conflicts you have between audition dates and show dates. Video auditions can be emailed to mattroot1274@gmail.com.

SYNOPSIS:
Tennessee Williams‚Äô The Glass Menagerie is a poignant memory play about family, dreams, and the painful tension between illusion and reality.

Set in a small St. Louis apartment during the 1930s, the story is narrated by Tom Wingfield, who looks back on his youth living with his domineering mother Amanda and his fragile, painfully shy sister Laura. Amanda, abandoned years earlier by her husband, clings to memories of her Southern belle past and is determined to secure a future for Laura, whose physical disability and extreme anxiety keep her isolated from the world.

Amanda pressures Tom, who longs to escape his monotonous warehouse job and pursue a life of adventure and writing, to bring home a ‚Äúgentleman caller‚Äù for Laura. When Tom finally invites his coworker Jim O‚ÄôConnor to dinner, the evening unfolds with hope, awkwardness, and heartbreak‚Äîforcing each character to confront their illusions and the limits of their dreams.

ROLES AVAILABLE:
Tom Wingfield (Male, 20s‚Äì30s)
Narrator / Son
A restless young man trapped between responsibility and desire for freedom. Tom works in a warehouse to support his family but dreams of becoming a poet and adventurer. He narrates the story from the future, reflecting on the guilt and longing he still carries after leaving his family behind.

Amanda Wingfield (Female, late 40s‚Äì60s)  Mother
A faded Southern belle clinging desperately to memories of her youth and the illusion of gentility. Amanda is controlling, talkative, and fiercely determined to secure a future for her children, especially Laura. Beneath her humor and bluster lies deep fear of abandonment and poverty.

Laura Wingfield (Female, late teens‚Äì20s)  Daughter
Extremely shy and emotionally fragile, Laura has a slight physical disability and crippling social anxiety. She escapes into her collection of delicate glass animals and old records. Gentle, kind, and painfully self-conscious, she embodies vulnerability and quiet hope.

Jim O‚ÄôConnor (Male, 20s‚Äì30s)
The Gentleman Caller
Tom‚Äôs coworker and Amanda‚Äôs long-awaited ‚Äúgentleman caller.‚Äù Once a popular high-school hero, Jim is now an ordinary young man with big dreams and relentless optimism. Kind and well-meaning, though sometimes unaware of the emotional impact he has on others.

Questions? Contact the director at mattroot1274@gmail.com.
